Left-side tower, the capital of the central semi column case"/></a><a href="http://www.archodessa.com/pictures/kirche-126.jpg"><img src="http://www.archodessa.com//pictures/thumbs//kirche-126.thumb.jpg" width="685" height="1000" alt="Left-side tower, the capital of the central semi column case"/></a><a href="http://www.archodessa.com/pictures/kirche-131.jpg"><img src="http://www.archodessa.com//pictures/thumbs//kirche-131.thumb.jpg" width="746" height="1000" alt="Left-side tower, the capital of the side semi column case"/></a></div>
<div class="txt-picture">
<img src="http://www.archodessa.com/pictures/kirche-history-12.jpg" width="1000" height="772" alt="Lutheran Church in Odessa. German church." />
<p>A view of the apse and the altar part tower shortly before the fire in 1976</p>
</div>
<p>Portals to the axis of the transept are made in the form of massive verandas, taken out  ​​of the range of the facade plane and decorated with medallions.</p>
